---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
const url = (href: string) => base + href;
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Recursio"
  description="How Recursio collects, uses, and protects user data, including learning data and AI-assisted practice content."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <article class="card legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: May 2026</p>

    <h2>1. Overview</h2>
    <p>
      Recursio is a language-learning app that helps users save vocabulary, review words, practice grammar, and use AI-assisted learning features. This Privacy Policy explains what information Recursio may collect, how it is used, and how users can request deletion of their account and learning data.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account information:</strong> sign-in provider, account identifier, and email address if provided by Apple or Google.</li>
      <li><strong>Learning data:</strong> saved words, vocabulary spaces, word states, grammar progress, practice history, recall progress, Coach sessions, AI Writing attempts, and related learning activity.</li>
      <li><strong>AI practice content:</strong> text the user submits to Coach, AI Writing, AI Grammar, and similar learning features.</li>
      <li><strong>Subscription status:</strong> plan level such as PRACTICE, SMART, or PRO, entitlement status, and store-related subscription identifiers required to unlock paid features.</li>
      <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> app version, device/platform type, crash or diagnostic information if enabled later.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Recursio does not directly collect payment card details. Payments are processed by the App Store or Google Play.
    </p>

    <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To provide saved vocabulary and learning progress.</li>
      <li>To personalize recall, grammar, and Coach practice.</li>
      <li>To generate AI feedback, explanations, and practice tasks.</li>
      <li>To manage subscription access.</li>
      <li>To improve reliability and fix technical issues.</li>
      <li>To respond to support requests.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. AI Processing</h2>
    <p>
      Some user-submitted text may be processed by AI service providers to generate feedback, corrections, explanations, practice prompts, or conversation responses.
    </p>
    <p>
      Users should not submit sensitive personal information in practice answers.
    </p>
    <p>
      AI feedback may be imperfect and should be treated as learning assistance, not as a guaranteed authoritative correction.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Purchases and Subscriptions</h2>
    <p>
      Subscription purchases are handled by Apple App Store or Google Play. Recursio receives subscription entitlement information needed to unlock paid features, but does not receive full payment card details.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Data Sharing</h2>
    <p>Recursio does not sell user personal data.</p>
    <p>
      Data may be shared only with service providers needed to operate the app, such as authentication providers, hosting providers, AI processing providers, app store payment systems, or support tools.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
      Account-linked learning data is retained while the user account remains active, unless the user requests deletion or unless retention is required for legal, security, or operational reasons.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Account and Data Deletion</h2>
    <p>
      Users can request deletion of their account and account-linked learning data through the <a href={url('/delete-account')}>Delete Account</a> page or by contacting <a href="mailto:support@recursio.app">support@recursio.app</a>.
    </p>
    <p>Deletion requests are processed within a reasonable period, typically within 30 days.</p>

    <h2>9. Children</h2>
    <p>
      Recursio is not intended for children under 13. If a parent or guardian believes a child has provided personal information, they should contact support.
    </p>

    <h2>10. International Users</h2>
    <p>
      Data may be processed in countries other than the user’s country of residence, depending on service providers.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      Recursio may update this Privacy Policy. The “Last updated” date will be changed when the policy is updated.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this Privacy Policy can be sent to <a href="mailto:support@recursio.app">support@recursio.app</a>.
    </p>

    <div class="accent-surface">
      <strong>Note:</strong> This document is a draft and should be reviewed by qualified legal counsel before publication. Legal entity details (company name, registration number, registered address) are placeholders and must be filled in before final use.
    </div>
  </article>
</LegalLayout>
